1
00:00:50,860 --> 00:00:52,487
So you’re always in front of the stage?

2
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:56,014
Watching the production
from the audience point of view.

3
00:00:57,057 --> 00:00:58,057
Right?

4
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:02,086
Are you interrogating me right now?

5
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:19,662
Get your hands off her!

6
00:01:20,622 --> 00:01:23,416
And once we have strong suspicion
of who it is,

7
00:01:23,527 --> 00:01:28,282
we need to lure our prey
out of his hiding hole to get evidence.

8
00:01:29,422 --> 00:01:30,507
That's not true.

9
00:01:33,438 --> 00:01:34,444
No!

10
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:37,097
My kids look so good!

11
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:38,598
So where’s your date?

12
00:01:38,723 --> 00:01:41,403
- Oh, we’re not going on a date, Tita!
- Just in a café at the mall.

13
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:47,665
So sorry to keep you waiting, Lori.

14
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:56,199
Remind me again.

15
00:01:57,742 --> 00:02:00,078
Why did you ask me
to pretend to be your boyfriend?

16
00:02:00,161 --> 00:02:01,216
- Draco?
- Draco?

17
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:02,747
- Draco!
- Are you okay?

18
00:02:02,772 --> 00:02:03,924
Sophie, what happened?

19
00:02:03,949 --> 00:02:05,751
- What's happening?
- What's happening? Are you okay?

20
00:02:05,775 --> 00:02:06,776
Hey!

21
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:08,779
Adriana! Wait, hold on!

22
00:02:10,605 --> 00:02:12,024
- Someone call an ambulance!
- He was eating donuts,

23
00:02:12,048 --> 00:02:13,591
and then he collapsed to the floor.

24
00:02:13,616 --> 00:02:15,117
Draco! Get up!

25
00:02:16,199 --> 00:02:17,199
Draco!

26
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:18,930
- Wait, wait.
- Help!

27
00:02:18,955 --> 00:02:21,232
- Sophie, get away!
- Draco!

28
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:26,312
What's happening?

29
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,439
He’s dead.

30
00:02:30,083 --> 00:02:31,334
Adriana, calm down.

31
00:02:31,359 --> 00:02:32,359
Stop!

32
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:34,154
Don’t touch anything!

33
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:36,270
This is now an active crime scene.

34
00:02:36,694 --> 00:02:37,737
Are you okay?

35
00:02:38,734 --> 00:02:41,713
I’m kind of used to
scenes like this, Al.

36
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:43,370
Used to it?

37
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:45,136
What do you mean, “used to it”?

38
00:02:45,915 --> 00:02:49,212
Loki and I are members
of the school’s detective club.

39
00:02:49,586 --> 00:02:52,297
That’s why I’m used
to encountering things like this.

40
00:03:05,018 --> 00:03:06,352
Detective club?

41
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,563
I didn’t know
you’re into that sort of thing.

42
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:14,616
Even I didn’t expect I’d get involved,
or end up liking this kind of club.

43
00:03:15,461 --> 00:03:17,338
We didn't... We...

44
00:03:17,363 --> 00:03:18,698
- Stop, stop.
- We didn't...

45
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:22,577
And who said you could step
onto the crime scene, kid?

46
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:32,003
Shadows

47
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:35,006
in the dark are crawling

48
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:39,761
Keeping watch and barring your way

49
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:43,306
As if the line could not be crossed

50
00:03:44,265 --> 00:03:47,852
To every scream and every tremor

51
00:03:47,852 --> 00:03:51,022
These walls remain the only witness

52
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:53,983
Every noise is etched in here

53
00:03:53,983 --> 00:03:58,488
Like fire and ammunition for your memory

54
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:01,991
Heed the warnings

55
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:05,620
The threats poised to strike

56
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:10,375
For this world

57
00:04:11,042 --> 00:04:13,670
is not what you imagined

58
00:04:13,670 --> 00:04:16,130
Heed the warnings

59
00:04:17,131 --> 00:04:19,259
Open up your eyes

60
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:24,097
For this world

61
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,350
is not what you imagined

62
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:32,188
Heed the warnings

63
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:34,607
Chief Tobias!

64
00:04:36,103 --> 00:04:37,943
It’s been so long
since we last saw each other.

65
00:04:38,945 --> 00:04:41,572
How long has it been
since we last solved our case together?

66
00:04:42,323 --> 00:04:44,158
You’re Estrada’s kid.

67
00:04:44,742 --> 00:04:47,662
We last crossed paths
at a crime scene last year.

68
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:53,835
Looks like even now, even here,
you’re still carrying your curse.

69
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:59,319
Looks like your boyfriend’s well-connected
with the cops, huh?

70
00:05:00,675 --> 00:05:03,386
Look, he’s not being kicked
out of the crime scene.

71
00:05:03,886 --> 00:05:05,596
They’re letting him investigate.

72
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:07,223
Does he have connections?

73
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:13,604
Even I don’t get
why he’s so influential with the cops.

74
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:17,400
Maybe he has a high-ranking relative?

75
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,208
I really want to chat
with you more, chief.

76
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:22,447
But there’s still a case
that needs to be solved.

77
00:05:22,744 --> 00:05:26,331
Chief, is it okay if I continue assisting
with the investigation?

78
00:05:27,127 --> 00:05:28,127
Of course.

79
00:05:28,310 --> 00:05:31,438
We need your skills for cases like this.

80
00:05:32,582 --> 00:05:34,042
Chief, I hope you don’t mind,

81
00:05:34,067 --> 00:05:37,558
if my colleague
would also help me in this case.

82
00:05:38,105 --> 00:05:39,773
So you’ve got a partner again now?

83
00:05:43,634 --> 00:05:45,178
She’s actually my girlfriend.

84
00:05:46,095 --> 00:05:49,515
And like me, she’s very observant.

85
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:53,770
Her insights have helped me a lot
in solving cases in school.

86
00:05:54,395 --> 00:05:55,938
You can ask Chief Estrada.

87
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:58,160
Um...

88
00:05:58,191 --> 00:06:01,361
Would you mind if I help out
with your investigation?

89
00:06:01,986 --> 00:06:03,279
Maybe I can help.

90
00:06:05,323 --> 00:06:06,532
If not, it’s okay.

91
00:06:07,864 --> 00:06:10,867
Very well,
you've proven yourself to be sharp.

92
00:06:11,638 --> 00:06:12,931
Would that be okay, chief?

93
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:17,126
We really don’t allow it
if you’re not in law enforcement.

94
00:06:17,835 --> 00:06:20,838
But since I owe your father a lot...

95
00:06:21,923 --> 00:06:24,759
And I know you’re good at this…

96
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:26,468
Fine.

97
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:28,179
I’ll allow you.

98
00:06:29,175 --> 00:06:30,635
You can count on us, chief.

99
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:34,142
Lorelei.

100
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:35,477
Thank you.

101
00:06:52,412 --> 00:06:54,539
Judging by the smell of almond
from his mouth,

102
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:59,043
the victim was poisoned
with Potassium Cyanide.

103
00:06:59,669 --> 00:07:03,798
Just from the smell, you concluded
that’s the poison that killed him?

104
00:07:04,132 --> 00:07:05,258
Loki's right.

105
00:07:06,342 --> 00:07:11,347
The almond scent isn’t the only sign
that Potassium Cyanide poisoned him.

106
00:07:12,448 --> 00:07:15,395
Potassium Cyanide
inhibits cellular respiration,

107
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:18,438
preventing tissues
from using oxygen from the blood.

108
00:07:19,397 --> 00:07:22,650
Anyone who ingests,
it will show bluish lips.

109
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:28,030
Gosh, where do you get
that kind of information?

110
00:07:28,700 --> 00:07:33,497
As far as I remember, we didn’t have
a toxicology subject in our courses.

111
00:07:35,163 --> 00:07:38,249
You mean you don't read books
that aren’t part of your curriculum?

112
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:40,460
There’s no problem with that.

113
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:43,129
Especially if you’re not interested
in toxicology.

114
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:47,717
That’s just what I came across
when I watched a documentary.

115
00:07:57,785 --> 00:07:59,829
- Hi! How are you?
- Hi! Hi, Draco!

116
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:01,397
- How are you?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

117
00:08:01,422 --> 00:08:02,846
I thought you weren’t coming.

118
00:08:02,871 --> 00:08:05,039
- Was it super traffic?
- Yeah, totally!

119
00:08:05,064 --> 00:08:06,899
Can we just move to a different table?

120
00:08:06,924 --> 00:08:08,766
- Let's just transfer.
- Yeah, sure.

121
00:08:11,949 --> 00:08:13,949
They’re the only ones
who had access to the victim.

122
00:08:16,221 --> 00:08:17,722
And one of them is the murderer.

123
00:08:17,845 --> 00:08:18,845
Huh?

124
00:08:18,870 --> 00:08:21,331
Why are we the ones you’re accusing?

125
00:08:21,459 --> 00:08:23,244
Draco is our friend!

126
00:08:23,347 --> 00:08:26,267
Of all people, we’d never do that to him!

127
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:27,965
Being his friend doesn’t mean

128
00:08:27,990 --> 00:08:30,785
that you can’t devise
an ingenious plan to kill him.

129
00:08:31,427 --> 00:08:32,427
Remember...

130
00:08:33,190 --> 00:08:37,236
Betrayal comes from your friends,
not from your enemies.

131
00:08:38,100 --> 00:08:41,437
Potassium Cyanide takes minutes
before it can kill someone.

132
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:46,400
Since you were with the victim
30 minutes before he collapsed,

133
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:50,071
you three are the primary suspects.

134
00:08:50,517 --> 00:08:52,853
There are so many people
in this café, right?

135
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:55,284
Why are you accusing us?

136
00:08:55,660 --> 00:08:57,787
Couldn’t it be the staff?

137
00:08:58,350 --> 00:09:00,623
Exactly. Why us?

138
00:09:00,669 --> 00:09:01,687
No.

139
00:09:01,758 --> 00:09:03,120
- Highly unlikely.
- No, it wasn't us

140
00:09:03,144 --> 00:09:06,439
Of all the customers here,
only Draco died.

141
00:09:06,655 --> 00:09:09,491
Which means the attack
was targeted at him.

142
00:09:09,832 --> 00:09:11,926
The culprit couldn’t guarantee

143
00:09:11,926 --> 00:09:14,804
the poisoned food or drink
would reach the victim

144
00:09:14,829 --> 00:09:16,189
if it had to go through the staff.

145
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:19,809
This would all be easier
if someone just confessed.

146
00:09:20,226 --> 00:09:22,645
Or someone might speak up
if they knew anything.

147
00:09:23,437 --> 00:09:27,984
Because until someone confesses,
we won’t be done here.

148
00:09:28,276 --> 00:09:30,111
And we’ll have to hold the three of you.

149
00:09:31,028 --> 00:09:33,322
We didn't do any... We didn't do anything.

150
00:09:34,782 --> 00:09:38,953
Are you really sure about your conclusion
that one of them killed Draco?

151
00:09:40,861 --> 00:09:42,529
Are you doubting my deduction skills?

152
00:09:42,748 --> 00:09:43,916
It’s not like that.

153
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:46,982
It’s just that we’re making
a serious accusation against them.

154
00:09:47,561 --> 00:09:49,689
What if they’re actually innocent?

155
00:09:50,122 --> 00:09:52,541
Then we’d just be adding to their trauma.

156
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,011
You have a point.

157
00:09:56,956 --> 00:09:58,791
But I'm confident in my deduction.

158
00:09:59,475 --> 00:10:00,601
It’s obvious.

159
00:10:01,118 --> 00:10:02,495
You can smell it a mile away.

160
00:10:03,063 --> 00:10:05,691
Sorry, Lori,
but I agree with your boyfriend.

161
00:10:06,396 --> 00:10:09,483
There are no other possible suspects
but the three of them.

162
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:12,194
Now, the real question is,

163
00:10:12,219 --> 00:10:14,096
which of the three did it?

164
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:16,657
And how do we make them confess?

165
00:10:17,908 --> 00:10:20,868
The way it looks, we might have a hard time
getting the culprit to confess.

166
00:10:29,339 --> 00:10:32,092
So, is anyone ready to confess?

167
00:10:32,400 --> 00:10:35,945
You know,
we’re just wasting our time here.

168
00:10:36,277 --> 00:10:38,779
None of us killed Draco.

169
00:10:38,857 --> 00:10:41,026
The four of us were on good terms.

170
00:10:41,244 --> 00:10:44,080
Draco treated us well,

171
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:47,504
that’s why we could
never do that to him.

172
00:10:48,239 --> 00:10:50,146
Why are you saying we killed him?

173
00:10:50,178 --> 00:10:52,305
What motive would we even have?

174
00:10:52,943 --> 00:10:54,820
The three of you liked him.

175
00:10:55,738 --> 00:10:56,738
Right?

176
00:10:57,031 --> 00:10:58,783
I don’t know the victim,

177
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:01,619
but I can clearly see it in your behavior

178
00:11:01,869 --> 00:11:03,913
and how you treated him.

179
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:09,126
I can clearly see in your eyes
how painful his loss is.

180
00:11:09,418 --> 00:11:11,087
But if my hunch is right,

181
00:11:11,862 --> 00:11:13,697
he was seeing each of you separately.

182
00:11:14,264 --> 00:11:17,015
But he didn’t want anything serious
with any of you.

183
00:11:17,425 --> 00:11:19,725
But if we’re looking for a motive,

184
00:11:20,335 --> 00:11:22,254
it’s probably connected to love.

185
00:11:22,709 --> 00:11:25,430
Because it’s one
of the strongest motivators

186
00:11:25,721 --> 00:11:27,807
for committing something so heinous.

187
00:11:27,895 --> 00:11:30,898
That’s such a shallow reason
to kill someone!

188
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:33,326
It’s better that we start investigating

189
00:11:33,351 --> 00:11:35,528
rather than wait for them to confess.

190
00:11:35,986 --> 00:11:36,986
For now,

191
00:11:37,988 --> 00:11:40,324
let’s have everything
on their table checked

192
00:11:40,783 --> 00:11:42,368
for traces of poison.

193
00:11:42,993 --> 00:11:44,370
They’re working on it now.

194
00:11:46,091 --> 00:11:47,525
Lorelei has a point.

195
00:11:47,748 --> 00:11:52,044
Honestly, I’ve handled
a lot of crimes of passion.

196
00:11:52,347 --> 00:11:56,310
You’d be surprised what people can do
in the name of love.

197
00:11:57,216 --> 00:11:58,216
See?

198
00:12:05,923 --> 00:12:08,050
So, who do you think did it?

199
00:12:09,376 --> 00:12:11,003
If you were observing them earlier,

200
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:13,392
you would no doubt have a guess
on who it might be.

201
00:12:13,527 --> 00:12:15,287
Have you been observing them
for a while now?

202
00:12:15,923 --> 00:12:17,904
Like you sensed something bad
was about to happen to them,

203
00:12:17,928 --> 00:12:19,221
so they caught your attention?

204
00:12:20,047 --> 00:12:21,132
No, no.

205
00:12:21,289 --> 00:12:25,626
We were just being nosy earlier
because we had nothing to do.

206
00:12:28,499 --> 00:12:30,459
We just observed them.

207
00:12:31,187 --> 00:12:34,857
But we heard some things
from their conversation

208
00:12:34,882 --> 00:12:38,344
that might help us find the truth.

209
00:12:38,878 --> 00:12:40,463
So going back to the question,

210
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,803
who do you think did it?

211
00:12:48,456 --> 00:12:49,583
- I think it’s--
- Wait!

212
00:12:50,722 --> 00:12:52,765
It’d be better if we write down

213
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:54,190
each of our guesses.

214
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:56,566
Huh?

215
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:05,450
Perfect.

216
00:13:10,372 --> 00:13:11,372
Why?

217
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,126
Each of us has a guess.

218
00:13:15,044 --> 00:13:16,837
If we tell each other,

219
00:13:17,171 --> 00:13:19,715
we might influence
each other’s conclusions.

220
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:21,342
What do you think?

221
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:23,219
I don’t think it’s a good idea.

222
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,263
Cases like this aren’t a game.

223
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:30,100
You must be fun at parties.

224
00:13:30,726 --> 00:13:31,726
Wow.

225
00:13:32,686 --> 00:13:33,686
Okay, listen.

226
00:13:34,563 --> 00:13:36,065
This isn’t just a game.

227
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:39,401
We’ll just see if one, two,

228
00:13:39,426 --> 00:13:41,387
or all three of us got the right answer.

229
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:44,572
Alright.

230
00:13:44,698 --> 00:13:46,992
We have to wait
until the lab results are out.

231
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:50,871
Unfortunately, that might take some time.

232
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:54,500
I’m dying to know
where they found the traces of poison.

233
00:13:54,834 --> 00:13:55,834
Wait.

234
00:13:56,210 --> 00:13:59,713
Didn’t you say we shouldn’t be influencing
each other’s guesses?

235
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:02,465
Fine!

236
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:04,844
Excuse me, I need to think.

237
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:18,278
I just wanted some time to relax.

238
00:14:18,774 --> 00:14:22,903
But why do we still have to solve a case
even here?

239
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:29,118
Looks like even now, even here,
you’re still carrying your curse.

240
00:14:29,492 --> 00:14:32,287
Maybe Loki really is cursed,

241
00:14:32,312 --> 00:14:35,941
that's why bad luck
follows him everywhere.

242
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:39,261
You won’t gain anything by joining that.

243
00:14:41,832 --> 00:14:44,485
Staying close to Loki
will only bring you tragedy.

244
00:14:45,968 --> 00:14:47,636
What if Maggie’s right?

245
00:14:49,096 --> 00:14:51,265
What if I end up like Rhea?

246
00:14:52,299 --> 00:14:53,675
- What if--
- Lorelei

247
00:14:53,924 --> 00:14:55,258
What’s taking you so long?

248
00:14:55,732 --> 00:14:57,484
Sorry. Here it is.

249
00:15:11,660 --> 00:15:13,036
According to my team,

250
00:15:13,061 --> 00:15:17,983
they found traces of Potassium Cyanide
on the handle of the victim’s teacup.

251
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:20,586
And on the tissues he used.

252
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:26,550
So if Potassium Cyanide
was traced on the teacup handle,

253
00:15:26,924 --> 00:15:30,219
that means the poison
wasn’t in what he drank.

254
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:33,057
It could’ve been in the donut he ate,

255
00:15:33,390 --> 00:15:36,185
or in something else
he touched on the table.

256
00:15:39,294 --> 00:15:40,378
How about his friends?

257
00:15:40,403 --> 00:15:41,689
That’s exactly what’s strange.

258
00:15:41,936 --> 00:15:47,150
No traces on the plates, teacups,
or even the tissues his friends used.

259
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,156
None at all?

260
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:51,200
It’s impossible for our lab
to make a mistake.

261
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:56,413
All items on the table
underwent testing, right?

262
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,786
Yes. We’re thorough with our methods.

263
00:15:58,933 --> 00:16:00,393
We didn’t miss a thing.

264
00:16:03,170 --> 00:16:04,672
- Chief, excuse me.
- Yes?

265
00:16:04,838 --> 00:16:07,883
Could you enumerate all the items
that were tested?

266
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:11,804
Four leftover donuts,
four teacups with black tea,

267
00:16:11,829 --> 00:16:15,332
four plates, crumpled tissues,
two sets of fork and knife.

268
00:16:15,849 --> 00:16:18,686
- Excuse us for a while, chief.
- Yeah. Go ahead. Get this.

269
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,774
Are we all thinking of the same thing?

270
00:16:25,919 --> 00:16:28,963
There are missing items
from those tested for poison traces.

271
00:16:28,988 --> 00:16:32,199
We can use that to figure out
who did this to Draco.

272
00:16:35,978 --> 00:16:38,230
It seems that we all have
a suspect in mind now.

273
00:16:38,622 --> 00:16:40,416
Let’s see if we all got it correctly.

274
00:16:41,475 --> 00:16:43,227
Should we show our answers?

275
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:44,252
Not yet.

276
00:16:45,087 --> 00:16:46,505
I’m going to do a magic trick.

277
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:50,426
And this will reveal the real culprit.

278
00:17:00,334 --> 00:17:01,377
He’s good.

279
00:17:02,104 --> 00:17:03,647
His methods are unusual.

280
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:07,443
Is that what you liked about him?

281
00:17:18,612 --> 00:17:19,612
What?

282
00:17:20,037 --> 00:17:22,164
Don’t you ever stop, huh?

283
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:26,014
We already told you,
the killer of Draco isn’t one of us!

284
00:17:26,535 --> 00:17:29,579
Actually, we already have a suspect.

285
00:17:30,657 --> 00:17:32,700
Before we reveal who she is,

286
00:17:33,218 --> 00:17:35,220
we want you to do something for us.

287
00:17:35,345 --> 00:17:37,598
What are we going to do with those donuts?

288
00:17:37,705 --> 00:17:41,083
We already lost a friend
and you still want us to eat donuts?

289
00:17:41,769 --> 00:17:43,444
How insensitive of you!

290
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:45,425
With the chief’s permission,

291
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:46,940
I’m going to use a method

292
00:17:46,940 --> 00:17:50,486
that will instantly
make the culprit confess.

293
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:52,820
I see.

294
00:17:55,282 --> 00:17:56,658
So that’s what he was going to do.

295
00:17:59,495 --> 00:18:01,413
All I’m asking is something simple.

296
00:18:02,597 --> 00:18:05,641
Eat your donuts then we’re done.

297
00:18:05,971 --> 00:18:10,517
And how are you supposed to figure out
who the killer is if we eat that donut?

298
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,132
It’s a magic trick.

299
00:18:12,434 --> 00:18:14,060
You’ll find out once we’re done.

300
00:18:14,711 --> 00:18:18,257
The process will go faster
if you cooperate with him.

301
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:20,140
It's an easy task.

302
00:18:20,534 --> 00:18:22,286
And those donuts aren’t poisoned.

303
00:18:23,265 --> 00:18:24,850
So, eat up!

304
00:18:28,191 --> 00:18:29,484
I said eat up.

305
00:18:43,914 --> 00:18:45,249
Is there something wrong, miss?

306
00:18:46,708 --> 00:18:48,752
Why aren’t you eating
the donut in front of you?

307
00:18:49,461 --> 00:18:52,683
With everything going on,
I don’t think I can eat right now.

308
00:18:56,014 --> 00:18:57,724
By eating your donuts,

309
00:18:57,749 --> 00:19:01,211
the two of you have proven your innocence.

310
00:19:03,337 --> 00:19:06,006
While you have shown guilt,

311
00:19:06,453 --> 00:19:07,746
by not eating yours.

312
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:11,233
Looks like we have the same suspect.

313
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:13,985
Me too!

314
00:19:14,862 --> 00:19:16,196
You didn’t eat the donut

315
00:19:16,510 --> 00:19:19,532
because you were afraid
that it was poisoned...

316
00:19:24,705 --> 00:19:25,705
Right?

317
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:28,500
And that also explains
why you used fork and knife

318
00:19:28,525 --> 00:19:29,985
while eating your donut.

319
00:19:31,587 --> 00:19:33,050
We were all together,

320
00:19:33,213 --> 00:19:37,009
how could she have poisoned
Draco’s food and drink?

321
00:19:37,182 --> 00:19:40,101
We didn't even see her touch those.

322
00:19:41,029 --> 00:19:44,449
We noticed something missing
from the list of items tested.

323
00:19:44,474 --> 00:19:45,726
Is there no creamer here?

324
00:19:45,976 --> 00:19:47,644
Alright, I’ll go get the creamer.

325
00:19:49,062 --> 00:19:53,066
Stacy volunteered
to get creamer for Draco, right?

326
00:19:56,559 --> 00:19:58,353
And since she was far from you,

327
00:19:58,797 --> 00:20:01,592
none of you noticed
Stacy had already transferred

328
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:04,369
the poison into the creamer sachet.

329
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:10,042
The moment your friend touched it,
his death warrant had been signed.

330
00:20:12,085 --> 00:20:13,712
Hey, smooth.

331
00:20:16,690 --> 00:20:19,484
And to avoid the poison
being detected on the fork and knife,

332
00:20:19,509 --> 00:20:21,053
she wiped them with tissue

333
00:20:21,078 --> 00:20:24,164
before the poison
could fully take effect on Draco.

334
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:43,616
Draco?

335
00:20:44,576 --> 00:20:45,576
Draco!

336
00:20:47,037 --> 00:20:49,414
Hey! Draco!

337
00:20:50,390 --> 00:20:51,768
- What happened?
- He was eating donuts

338
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:54,032
- and then he collapsed to the floor.
- What's happening?

339
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:56,880
If you’re looking for evidence,

340
00:20:57,381 --> 00:20:59,174
why don’t we ask Stacy?

341
00:20:59,816 --> 00:21:02,861
Let’s find the creamer sachets

342
00:21:02,886 --> 00:21:05,889
and the tissues she used
to wipe the fork and knife.

343
00:21:10,672 --> 00:21:12,508
Is it okay if we check your bag?

344
00:21:15,023 --> 00:21:16,108
No need!

345
00:21:16,439 --> 00:21:18,691
Really, Stacy?

346
00:21:19,695 --> 00:21:21,110
You really did it?

347
00:21:22,080 --> 00:21:24,374
Yeah! It was me!

348
00:21:25,242 --> 00:21:27,452
I'm the one who poisoned Draco.

349
00:21:29,201 --> 00:21:31,399
When I was in the restroom
before he arrived,

350
00:21:32,612 --> 00:21:35,365
I already put Potassium Cyanide
on my hands.

351
00:21:36,813 --> 00:21:39,554
The creamer sachets, the tissues...

352
00:21:39,598 --> 00:21:42,809
They're true.
Everything they said is true.

353
00:21:43,019 --> 00:21:44,762
Why did you do it, Stacy?

354
00:21:45,446 --> 00:21:47,698
Because I couldn’t let him
be with someone else!

355
00:21:48,811 --> 00:21:51,605
Here! Right here in this café!

356
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:54,104
This is where I confessed
everything to him!

357
00:21:56,546 --> 00:21:57,588
Stacy!

358
00:21:58,055 --> 00:21:59,928
- Hey! Draco!
- Hi!

359
00:22:00,755 --> 00:22:01,881
- Hi.
- Hi.

360
00:22:01,906 --> 00:22:03,450
Good thing you came.

361
00:22:03,653 --> 00:22:04,904
Yeah. How are you?

362
00:22:05,326 --> 00:22:06,494
I’m okay.

363
00:22:07,016 --> 00:22:08,476
- You look beautiful!
- Cool, huh?

364
00:22:09,910 --> 00:22:11,584
So, why did you
suddenly ask me out for tea?

365
00:22:11,608 --> 00:22:13,684
Excuse me. Here’s your order, sir.

366
00:22:13,764 --> 00:22:16,617
- Wow. Thank you.
- Your favorite, right?

367
00:22:17,380 --> 00:22:18,525
I made sure of it.

368
00:22:19,174 --> 00:22:20,216
Thank you.

369
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:24,032
I noticed you’re not
with Adriana and Sophie.

370
00:22:25,013 --> 00:22:28,031
I just wanted it to be just the two of us.

371
00:22:29,825 --> 00:22:30,951
And there’s something...

372
00:22:32,319 --> 00:22:34,280
There's something I want to tell you.

373
00:22:35,328 --> 00:22:37,205
Okay, go ahead. What is it?

374
00:22:38,401 --> 00:22:39,401
Um...

375
00:22:45,027 --> 00:22:47,280
Hey! What is it?

376
00:22:48,842 --> 00:22:50,469
Draco, I love you...

377
00:22:53,166 --> 00:22:54,459
I like you, Draco.

378
00:22:54,709 --> 00:22:56,252
I really, really like you.

379
00:22:57,003 --> 00:22:59,088
My feelings have gotten too strong.

380
00:22:59,355 --> 00:23:03,609
Maybe it’s better if I just tell you.

381
00:23:04,980 --> 00:23:05,980
Um...

382
00:23:07,180 --> 00:23:09,557
Stacy, honestly,

383
00:23:10,149 --> 00:23:12,575
I really appreciate you a lot.

384
00:23:12,987 --> 00:23:16,949
And I just want to thank you
for everything you’ve done for me.

385
00:23:18,438 --> 00:23:24,986
But I think you already know
that I can only offer you my friendship.

386
00:23:29,382 --> 00:23:30,382
Ah...

387
00:23:33,266 --> 00:23:34,862
- Okay.
- Stacy, I'm sorry.

388
00:23:38,317 --> 00:23:40,199
Why, Draco?

389
00:23:41,493 --> 00:23:43,161
Don’t you love me too?

390
00:23:44,868 --> 00:23:46,828
Can’t you love me too?

391
00:23:47,155 --> 00:23:48,448
It’s not like that.

392
00:23:49,996 --> 00:23:51,456
Is there someone else, Draco?

393
00:23:51,481 --> 00:23:53,107
Do you like someone else?

394
00:23:54,659 --> 00:23:55,702
What is it?

395
00:23:57,981 --> 00:23:59,959
He didn’t answer my question.

396
00:24:01,776 --> 00:24:05,375
Maybe he likes one of you.

397
00:24:06,795 --> 00:24:09,865
Maybe that’s why
he couldn’t reciprocate my feelings.

398
00:24:10,871 --> 00:24:14,055
Are you serious? That’s why?

399
00:24:16,749 --> 00:24:19,586
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

400
00:24:19,900 --> 00:24:22,653
I can’t handle knowing that.

401
00:24:23,506 --> 00:24:27,468
That’s why it’s better I did this now
instead of losing him to someone else!

402
00:24:29,137 --> 00:24:31,222
You’re wrong, Stacy.

403
00:24:31,447 --> 00:24:34,909
I’ve already confessed
my feelings to him before.

404
00:24:35,291 --> 00:24:40,338
But that’s when I found out,
you’re the one he really likes.

405
00:24:40,616 --> 00:24:41,616
Huh?

406
00:24:42,819 --> 00:24:45,906
- What? When was that?
- Sophie.

407
00:24:48,854 --> 00:24:51,857
The only reason Draco won’t confess

408
00:24:52,259 --> 00:24:55,595
is he doesn’t want
to ruin our friendship.

409
00:24:57,847 --> 00:25:00,183
And you got it all wrong, Stacy.

410
00:25:03,896 --> 00:25:06,065
You have the right to remain silent.

411
00:25:06,090 --> 00:25:10,219
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

412
00:25:10,219 --> 00:25:14,432
You have the right to have
a competent and independent counsel.

413
00:25:14,432 --> 00:25:17,393
If you cannot afford
the services of counsel,

414
00:25:17,393 --> 00:25:19,646
the government will provide one for you.

415
00:25:19,646 --> 00:25:21,939
- No. No.
- Do you understand your rights?

416
00:25:21,939 --> 00:25:23,608
- Come on. Come on, ma'am.
- Sophie! Adriana!

417
00:25:23,608 --> 00:25:25,193
- Sophie.
- We'll help you, okay?

418
00:25:25,193 --> 00:25:26,694
Alright. Please come with us now.

419
00:25:30,749 --> 00:25:33,701
That Loki is a remarkable man.

420
00:25:35,370 --> 00:25:38,331
Not everyone that age
can solve a case like this.

421
00:25:42,043 --> 00:25:43,252
He sure is unique.

422
00:25:44,921 --> 00:25:47,715
Imagine him acting
like a detective every day.

423
00:25:48,424 --> 00:25:49,967
That’s just how he is at school.

424
00:25:51,427 --> 00:25:52,553
So...

425
00:25:53,388 --> 00:25:55,139
how did you get him
to agree to this setup?

426
00:25:56,349 --> 00:25:57,349
Setup?

427
00:25:58,226 --> 00:25:59,394
What do you mean "setup"?

428
00:26:00,269 --> 00:26:02,480
You really think I
wouldn’t figure that out?

429
00:26:04,857 --> 00:26:06,484
When something bad happens,

430
00:26:07,151 --> 00:26:09,362
a person’s first instinct

431
00:26:10,321 --> 00:26:12,001
is always to check
on the person they love.

432
00:26:13,241 --> 00:26:15,326
But when the victim collapsed earlier...

433
00:26:15,326 --> 00:26:17,578
- that was the first thing he checked.
- Adriana, wait!

434
00:26:17,578 --> 00:26:19,663
- Not once did he ask you
- Draco! Help!

435
00:26:19,688 --> 00:26:21,416
if you were okay during the investigation.

436
00:26:22,458 --> 00:26:24,502
He treats you like a colleague,
not a girlfriend.

437
00:26:28,673 --> 00:26:29,799
You got me.

438
00:26:31,161 --> 00:26:33,163
You didn’t have to put on a show, Lori.

439
00:26:34,163 --> 00:26:35,582
Why did you do it?

440
00:26:37,281 --> 00:26:39,367
Why did you even come here?

441
00:26:40,207 --> 00:26:45,005
If you just wanted to check on me,
you could’ve just called or video chatted.

442
00:26:45,796 --> 00:26:47,631
You didn’t have to come all the way here.

443
00:26:49,527 --> 00:26:55,324
I came here to tell you that if you want
to go back to Manila, you can.

444
00:26:56,078 --> 00:26:58,851
You don’t have to worry
about "those people" anymore, Lori.

445
00:27:00,371 --> 00:27:01,423
What do you mean?

446
00:27:02,697 --> 00:27:07,062
Your dad did everything he could
to get them expelled from St. Barths.

447
00:27:08,374 --> 00:27:13,444
I know it’s a big adjustment getting used
to this place and feeling at home here.

448
00:27:14,093 --> 00:27:19,515
But if you decide you want
to go back to Manila, you can.

449
00:27:23,102 --> 00:27:24,687
There’s no more threat to you, Lori.

450
00:27:25,834 --> 00:27:26,835
You’re safe.

451
00:27:31,787 --> 00:27:34,289
I want to stay. Alright?

452
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:36,085
I’m doing okay here.

453
00:27:37,020 --> 00:27:41,900
People are nice, and the food’s great.

454
00:27:43,522 --> 00:27:45,941
The air is cleaner here than back home.

455
00:27:49,545 --> 00:27:50,546
It’s okay.

456
00:27:52,467 --> 00:27:54,553
Do you plan to stay here permanently?

457
00:27:56,928 --> 00:28:00,014
Maybe someday, I’ll go back to Manila.

458
00:28:01,211 --> 00:28:03,005
But not right now.

459
00:28:05,312 --> 00:28:06,566
I'm sorry, Al.

460
00:28:07,878 --> 00:28:08,920
Don’t be.

461
00:28:10,039 --> 00:28:12,125
I expected that’s what you’d say.

462
00:28:12,824 --> 00:28:15,035
But I just had to try.

463
00:28:16,199 --> 00:28:17,909
I was hoping you'd change your mind.

464
00:28:19,403 --> 00:28:21,864
But it's okay. I respect your decision.

465
00:28:23,145 --> 00:28:24,730
And I hope you’re happy here

466
00:28:26,833 --> 00:28:28,709
Thank you for understanding.

467
00:28:30,253 --> 00:28:31,379
Look...

468
00:28:31,921 --> 00:28:35,899
I still wanna have chat
with you and your "boyfriend."

469
00:28:37,760 --> 00:28:40,221
But I have to go back to Manila.

470
00:28:40,446 --> 00:28:42,948
You know how bad the traffic is
going back there.

471
00:28:44,591 --> 00:28:46,009
Have a safe trip back.

472
00:28:46,894 --> 00:28:47,894
Yeah.

473
00:28:48,554 --> 00:28:50,639
I’m glad we got to see each other again.

474
00:28:51,899 --> 00:28:53,192
Take care, okay?

475
00:28:54,610 --> 00:28:55,610
You too.

476
00:28:57,154 --> 00:28:58,489
I’ll be back here soon.

477
00:29:12,128 --> 00:29:13,128
Loki!

478
00:29:13,867 --> 00:29:17,523
I still wanna stay here
but I have to go back to Manila.

479
00:29:18,441 --> 00:29:20,777
You know I might get stuck in traffic
on the way there.

480
00:29:21,387 --> 00:29:22,847
Oh, you’re leaving.

481
00:29:23,639 --> 00:29:24,807
Have a safe trip back.

482
00:29:29,478 --> 00:29:30,478
And, please...

483
00:29:31,074 --> 00:29:32,659
take good care of my friend for me.

484
00:29:42,151 --> 00:29:45,738
He knows the truth
that we’re just pretending.

485
00:29:48,123 --> 00:29:49,230
Not surprised, though.

486
00:29:50,166 --> 00:29:52,457
Pleased to meet you. I'm Alistair Ravena.

487
00:29:53,022 --> 00:29:54,148
Loki Mendez.

488
00:29:54,173 --> 00:29:56,342
You’re lucky you won Lori’s heart.

489
00:29:58,507 --> 00:29:59,592
Do you mind?

490
00:30:00,985 --> 00:30:02,445
He tried to check earlier

491
00:30:02,470 --> 00:30:05,446
if there were any irregularities
in my pulse.

492
00:30:05,825 --> 00:30:07,368
Are you really Lorelei’s boyfriend?

493
00:30:07,742 --> 00:30:09,869
He even checked if my pupils dilated

494
00:30:09,894 --> 00:30:11,938
when he asked
if I was really your boyfriend.

495
00:30:16,243 --> 00:30:17,953
That’s a lie-detecting technique.

496
00:30:18,878 --> 00:30:20,546
I realized it a bit too late.

497
00:30:21,822 --> 00:30:24,784
Well, you do have an interesting friend.

498
00:30:26,617 --> 00:30:29,078
So why did you want me to pretend
to be your boyfriend?

499
00:30:30,294 --> 00:30:31,644
You wanna make him jealous?

500
00:30:33,374 --> 00:30:36,877
He’s not just a friend to you,
he’s much more than that.

501
00:30:37,478 --> 00:30:40,661
No, I wasn’t trying
to make him jealous.

502
00:30:42,551 --> 00:30:44,136
When we were still in Manila,

503
00:30:45,083 --> 00:30:51,882
he’s always there to protect me
and save me when I’m in danger.

504
00:30:53,729 --> 00:30:55,272
I just wanted to let him know

505
00:30:55,991 --> 00:30:58,327
that I don’t need him to save me anymore.

506
00:31:01,237 --> 00:31:03,906
Because there’s someone else
who can protect me now.

507
00:31:16,246 --> 00:31:19,698
Sometimes, our feelings
can get the best of us.

508
00:31:19,861 --> 00:31:23,657
This particular case is a warning
to guarding our hearts...

509
00:31:25,187 --> 00:31:27,773
so we won’t do anything
we'll regret in the end.

510
00:31:28,023 --> 00:31:32,027
After all, as they say,
"too much love can kill you."

511
00:31:34,629 --> 00:31:36,088
But the absence of love?

512
00:31:37,115 --> 00:31:39,034
Could it make one a killer?

513
00:32:02,006 --> 00:32:03,049
No.

514
00:32:03,966 --> 00:32:05,593
- Lori, come on.
- No.

515
00:32:05,593 --> 00:32:08,804
- Lori, come with us.
- No.

516
00:32:08,804 --> 00:32:09,847
Come with us.

517
00:32:09,847 --> 00:32:12,224
Get away from me!

518
00:32:12,224 --> 00:32:14,602
- Come on!
- Get away from me!

519
00:32:14,602 --> 00:32:16,562
Come here, Lori.

520
00:32:17,521 --> 00:32:19,482
- Come with us.
- Help!

521
00:32:25,446 --> 00:32:26,489
Come with us.

522
00:32:27,656 --> 00:32:28,656
Lori!

523
00:32:31,266 --> 00:32:33,476
Lorelei! Lorelei! Lorelei!

524
00:32:34,645 --> 00:32:36,647
Lorelei, it’s me.

525
00:32:37,662 --> 00:32:39,260
It's me, it's me. It's me, Loki.

526
00:32:40,628 --> 00:32:41,629
Lorelei...

527
00:32:42,713 --> 00:32:43,756
are you okay?

528
00:32:44,340 --> 00:32:46,717
I heard you screaming, so I came in.

529
00:32:49,345 --> 00:32:50,346
It’s okay.

530
00:32:53,265 --> 00:32:54,308
It’s me.

531
00:32:56,352 --> 00:32:57,561
It’s me, Loki.

532
00:33:10,627 --> 00:33:11,627
Don’t worry...

533
00:33:12,130 --> 00:33:15,342
nightmares are just your brain
running a simulation

534
00:33:15,434 --> 00:33:17,061
with bad graphics.

535
00:33:19,166 --> 00:33:22,628
Nothing to fear,
it’s all code in your neural network.

536
00:33:29,093 --> 00:33:30,093
Here.

537
00:33:31,554 --> 00:33:32,596
Have some tea.

538
00:33:34,014 --> 00:33:35,014
Don’t worry.

539
00:33:35,783 --> 00:33:39,161
It’s basically a warm infusion
of plant molecules

540
00:33:40,128 --> 00:33:42,964
designed to calm your nervous system.

541
00:33:50,386 --> 00:33:51,721
Thank you, Loki.

542
00:34:07,055 --> 00:34:10,684
Girl, you’re all anyone’s talking about
here at Clark U right now!

543
00:34:10,983 --> 00:34:12,942
Really? Why?

544
00:34:12,970 --> 00:34:16,891
Everyone’s heard about the cases
you solved at the other university,

545
00:34:16,891 --> 00:34:19,268
that student at the café who got poisoned.

546
00:34:19,268 --> 00:34:20,394
I see.

547
00:34:20,419 --> 00:34:23,923
Some students from Clark U were there,
they saw the incident.

548
00:34:23,970 --> 00:34:25,249
Well, that explains it.

549
00:34:25,274 --> 00:34:28,654
That explains why people I pass by
keep staring at me.

550
00:34:30,838 --> 00:34:33,882
Lori! Congratulations!

551
00:34:34,074 --> 00:34:38,663
I heard you did an amazing job
with that case

552
00:34:38,795 --> 00:34:41,711
about the student who
got poisoned at the café?

553
00:34:42,898 --> 00:34:46,610
But I’m pretty sure
that Loki did all the work!

554
00:34:47,883 --> 00:34:49,571
The weather’s nice.

555
00:34:51,634 --> 00:34:55,346
Anyway, I’ll see you
at the Q.E.D. club room.

556
00:34:55,804 --> 00:34:58,140
I already quit Clark Repertory.

557
00:34:58,505 --> 00:35:01,174
It’s because I’m not comfortable anymore
after what happened.

558
00:35:01,785 --> 00:35:03,954
He even asked me to go
to the club room later--

559
00:35:03,979 --> 00:35:06,899
Wait, Loki accepted you into Q.E.D.?

560
00:35:07,178 --> 00:35:08,220
Yes.

561
00:35:08,357 --> 00:35:14,212
He said I’d be a big help to the club
because of my photographic memory.

562
00:35:15,817 --> 00:35:17,807
Oh, I’ll go ahead.

563
00:35:17,906 --> 00:35:20,283
My class will start in a few minutes.

564
00:35:21,654 --> 00:35:22,654
See you!

565
00:35:25,751 --> 00:35:27,809
That’s so unfair!

566
00:35:27,834 --> 00:35:30,045
Why did she get in and not me?

567
00:35:31,382 --> 00:35:32,716
Don’t blame me!

568
00:35:32,741 --> 00:35:35,661
I mean, I’m not the club's president.

569
00:35:36,845 --> 00:35:37,888
Come on!

570
00:35:38,235 --> 00:35:40,115
Come on! Our class
will start in a few minutes.

571
00:35:45,346 --> 00:35:47,181
It’s an improvement, huh?

572
00:35:48,964 --> 00:35:50,340
De Los Santos...

573
00:35:52,598 --> 00:35:53,974
Pass it, please.

574
00:35:55,131 --> 00:35:58,217
Ms. Rios, congratulations!

575
00:35:58,242 --> 00:36:00,117
You got the highest score in our exam.

576
00:36:02,230 --> 00:36:03,398
Alright, class.

577
00:36:04,029 --> 00:36:07,824
Next time, do better on the exam.
Try to be like Ms. Rios.

578
00:36:10,813 --> 00:36:12,439
Cool. That's so good!

579
00:36:12,464 --> 00:36:14,425
How can they do that?

580
00:36:14,425 --> 00:36:16,969
Right? How can they do that?

581
00:36:16,969 --> 00:36:19,805
I just heard them playing.
I thought it's chess.

582
00:36:19,805 --> 00:36:23,058
Bro, check this out. That’s insane!

583
00:36:23,058 --> 00:36:24,935
- How can they do that?
- Solid!

584
00:36:26,520 --> 00:36:27,813
Think about it, how?

585
00:36:29,970 --> 00:36:32,138
Excuse me, coming through.

586
00:36:33,530 --> 00:36:35,199
- So good.
- Rook to C1.

587
00:36:36,822 --> 00:36:38,198
Pawn to E5.

588
00:36:38,490 --> 00:36:39,783
Pawn to C4.

589
00:36:40,034 --> 00:36:41,327
Knight to F3.

590
00:36:43,245 --> 00:36:44,663
Pawn to D5.

591
00:36:45,039 --> 00:36:46,498
Knight to C3.

592
00:36:49,228 --> 00:36:53,190
What are you guys doing?
Why do you look so serious?

593
00:36:55,382 --> 00:36:56,884
We’re playing game of Kings.

594
00:36:57,375 --> 00:36:59,336
Chess, in layman’s term.

595
00:37:00,767 --> 00:37:04,395
Chess? How are you playing
without a chessboard?

596
00:37:05,967 --> 00:37:07,844
The chessboard is in our minds.

597
00:37:07,924 --> 00:37:10,343
That’s what we call blindfold chess.

598
00:37:10,822 --> 00:37:15,160
No clients have come in yet,
so we decided to play.

599
00:37:15,863 --> 00:37:18,366
I also wanna test her photographic memory.

600
00:37:18,921 --> 00:37:20,973
I want to see if she still remembers

601
00:37:21,063 --> 00:37:24,185
where our imaginary pieces are
on the chessboard.

602
00:37:24,508 --> 00:37:26,761
And we’ve got a bet on this game.

603
00:37:27,114 --> 00:37:30,867
If I win, we’re having lunch later.

604
00:37:31,216 --> 00:37:33,276
So, I can’t afford to lose.

605
00:37:33,796 --> 00:37:35,172
Right, Loki?

606
00:37:37,299 --> 00:37:38,299
No…

607
00:37:39,172 --> 00:37:41,144
I prefer to have my lunch alone.

608
00:37:43,690 --> 00:37:45,108
Bishop to E7.

609
00:37:47,005 --> 00:37:50,258
Oops, sorry!

610
00:37:53,148 --> 00:37:55,359
Hello! Jamie speaking.

611
00:37:55,646 --> 00:37:57,023
Really, ma’am?

612
00:37:57,719 --> 00:38:01,431
I almost forgot. Okay, okay. See you.

613
00:38:04,118 --> 00:38:06,412
Sorry, but we have to postpone the game.

614
00:38:06,581 --> 00:38:08,958
I’m being called to the faculty room.

615
00:38:09,748 --> 00:38:12,751
Let’s just continue our game later, Loki.

616
00:38:12,969 --> 00:38:15,347
Don’t forget what we talked about, okay?

617
00:38:15,838 --> 00:38:17,256
Don’t forget.

618
00:38:18,090 --> 00:38:20,092
See you later, Lorelei.

619
00:38:22,553 --> 00:38:24,346
We’ll see each other later.

620
00:38:25,013 --> 00:38:27,471
Don’t try anything on Loki, alright?

621
00:38:31,103 --> 00:38:32,804
Bye, Loki!

622
00:38:38,420 --> 00:38:39,838
Are you and Jamie okay?

623
00:38:41,071 --> 00:38:45,492
Of course. We’re okay.

624
00:38:46,535 --> 00:38:47,656
I don’t think so.

625
00:38:49,572 --> 00:38:52,617
You seemed visibly uncomfortable.

626
00:38:54,457 --> 00:38:56,542
When she gave you a cheek-to-cheek,

627
00:38:57,171 --> 00:38:58,630
you looked so shocked.

628
00:38:59,815 --> 00:39:02,193
There's a palpable tension
between you two.

629
00:39:03,844 --> 00:39:04,928
No.

630
00:39:05,177 --> 00:39:07,471
I’m just not used to Jamie yet.

631
00:39:09,486 --> 00:39:11,787
- Anyway, I’ll go ahead.
- Okay.

632
00:39:12,669 --> 00:39:15,755
I’ve got you some coffee to wake you up.

633
00:39:32,182 --> 00:39:36,144
Loki, maybe you could help me clean up?

634
00:39:36,540 --> 00:39:37,833
Just maybe.

635
00:39:40,356 --> 00:39:41,649
I can’t hear you.

636
00:39:41,897 --> 00:39:44,608
I said, can you help me clean up?

637
00:39:58,415 --> 00:40:00,918
So, are you going to help me clean up?

638
00:40:01,245 --> 00:40:03,033
I’m always the one doing this.

639
00:40:03,753 --> 00:40:05,046
Hello?

640
00:40:06,156 --> 00:40:08,534
- Loki.
- What? I can’t hear you!

641
00:40:11,730 --> 00:40:13,987
I said, I’m always the one cleaning here,

642
00:40:14,199 --> 00:40:16,368
so maybe you could help me out, right?

643
00:40:16,857 --> 00:40:18,736
I even take out the trash myself.

644
00:40:22,589 --> 00:40:24,591
Loki, you're disgusting!

645
00:40:27,594 --> 00:40:29,546
You’re still that upset about Jamie, huh?

646
00:40:31,515 --> 00:40:33,725
Is it because I allowed her
to be part of the club?

647
00:40:36,203 --> 00:40:39,790
You know, it’s your right
as club president,

648
00:40:39,815 --> 00:40:42,776
so I don’t really care.

649
00:40:44,752 --> 00:40:48,672
Look, Jamie would be
a valuable addition to the club.

650
00:40:49,492 --> 00:40:52,578
She won’t be a burden, so I let her join.

651
00:40:52,869 --> 00:40:54,371
Is that really the reason?

652
00:40:55,122 --> 00:40:56,957
Or is it because she looks like Rhea?

653
00:41:03,839 --> 00:41:06,237
So, you’re admitting
that you’re upset with Jamie?

654
00:41:08,239 --> 00:41:10,100
It’s not that I don’t like Jamie,

655
00:41:10,441 --> 00:41:12,507
but there’s something off about her.

656
00:41:13,020 --> 00:41:14,939
Because when we were investigating--

657
00:41:17,144 --> 00:41:18,729
You’re a detective, right?

658
00:41:19,060 --> 00:41:21,491
If you can do imaginary chess,

659
00:41:21,898 --> 00:41:23,734
you should figure this out.

660
00:41:27,624 --> 00:41:29,042
I still have something to work on,

661
00:41:29,075 --> 00:41:31,808
so I won’t have time to delve
into your business with her.

662
00:41:32,861 --> 00:41:34,821
I thought you didn’t have
any clients earlier.

663
00:41:37,414 --> 00:41:39,708
No, it’s a personal request to me.

664
00:41:40,250 --> 00:41:41,793
And I can’t involve our club.

665
00:41:42,836 --> 00:41:44,296
I have to handle it by myself.

666
00:42:38,392 --> 00:42:39,434
Jamie?

667
00:42:41,250 --> 00:42:42,585
Where’s Loki?

668
00:42:43,413 --> 00:42:44,497
Lorelei…

669
00:42:47,442 --> 00:42:48,777
Loki…

670
00:42:58,796 --> 00:43:00,840
Hey, you there!

671
00:43:01,790 --> 00:43:03,500
Why don’t we play a game?

672
00:43:04,171 --> 00:43:05,840
Can’t find him anywhere?

673
00:43:06,443 --> 00:43:07,819
Oh, what a shame!

674
00:43:08,516 --> 00:43:10,143
I will give you time.

675
00:43:11,004 --> 00:43:12,839
Is 45 minutes fine?

676
00:43:14,145 --> 00:43:18,107
Better hurry up
'cause his life is on the line!

677
00:43:45,398 --> 00:43:46,558
Why?

678
00:43:47,552 --> 00:43:48,552
What’s going on?

679
00:43:48,734 --> 00:43:52,715
I apologize, in case,
my actions offended you.

680
00:43:53,057 --> 00:43:57,112
I was looking forward
to spending that afternoon with him.

681
00:43:57,137 --> 00:44:00,128
Why did it have to be him? Why not you?

682
00:44:00,879 --> 00:44:02,089
I get you, girl.

683
00:44:02,753 --> 00:44:05,464
It’s really hard being caught
in the middle of your emotions.

684
00:44:06,454 --> 00:44:08,908
You don’t even know
which one to fully give in to.

685
00:44:08,944 --> 00:44:11,947
Jamie, what if they find Loki
but it’s already too late?

686
00:44:15,658 --> 00:44:17,952
May I speak to Chief Estrada?

687
00:44:17,979 --> 00:44:20,457
Sorry, the chief isn’t here right now.

688
00:44:20,705 --> 00:44:22,164
He has a meeting with the president.

689
00:44:22,189 --> 00:44:25,894
Please, can you call him?
This is an emergency.

690
00:44:25,975 --> 00:44:28,853
If you remember it,
then write it down on paper.

691
00:44:29,127 --> 00:44:30,754
Please, we're running out of time.

692
00:44:30,937 --> 00:44:32,505
Don't you get it, Lorelei?

693
00:44:32,689 --> 00:44:34,107
We’ll just waste more time,

694
00:44:34,132 --> 00:44:37,928
if we keep trying to crack a code
that’s not even our expertise.

695
00:44:37,953 --> 00:44:41,039
You’re the only one
we can think of turning to.

696
00:44:42,599 --> 00:44:44,643
Can you crack that code?

697
00:44:51,527 --> 00:44:53,028
It doesn't make sense.

698
00:44:54,265 --> 00:44:56,601
Maybe we just used the wrong cipher.

699
00:45:03,411 --> 00:45:08,041
Jamie, this is your opportunity
to use your photographic memory.

700
00:45:13,706 --> 00:45:14,963
Stop--
